</media>
<para id="fs-idm201037984">What is the annual financial impact of hiring the extra worker for the bottleneck process?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm217591584">
<problem id="fs-idm196517648">
<para id="fs-idm212903664"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68086"/>Sports Specialists makes baseballs and softballs in a three-step process. Unfortunately, the sewing machine process has been identified as a bottleneck. Each softball has a contribution margin of $6.00 and each baseball has a contribution margin of $2.00. The sewing machine can make 10 softballs or 25 baseballs in one hour.</para>
<list id="fs-idm203740256" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha"><item>If demand for both products is unlimited and the sewing machine capacity cannot be expanded, which product should be produced?</item>
